subSubSection.paragraph:
Representatives of this species differ from congeners by the labium twice as wide as long with few cuspules (fewer than 15) (
Figure 3A
). Female representatives can be distinguished by the spermathecae receptacula as wide as long with several apical lobes (
Figure 3D
). Male representatives can be distinguished by the curved embolus of the palpal bulb (
Figure 3B, C
).
